        public java.lang.String getPathParam(java.lang.String paramName,
                                     java.lang.String target)
        Retrieves the path component specified by the key used in a Path annotation. If the key has no mapping match or the index is outside of the retrievable params list range, it will return null
        Parameters:
        paramName - A String key to retrieve a path component for
        target - A HTTP target from an instance of HTTPRequestStartLine
        Returns:
        Path component matchting the paramName key, or null if it does not exist
